  • Method Details

    • init

      public PagedQueryIterator init(int visibleRow)
      Returns an iterator positioned at the visible row index specified. If the rows preceding 'visibleRow' have not previously been loaded, by this iterator, the row this iterator is positioned at will be estimated on the assumption that no preceding rows are filtered.
      Parameters:
      visibleRow - the row to position this iterator at, based on the filtered results from Solr.
      Returns:
      self
      Throws:
      FetchLimitExceededException - if while searching for the existence of the next viewable result, the Solr fetch limit of this iterator was exceeded.

    • setFetchLimit

      public void setFetchLimit(int fetchLimit)
      Set the maximum number of sequential rows this iterator will request from Solr if, within those rows, no viewable results are found. This means the results are being filtered by post processing, such as contact that match but refer to null claims. Defaults to 300. If set to a huge number (e.g. MAX_INT) for a query with a large result set that is not viewable, the iterator will take a very long time to return from init() or next(). This is because it will page through most or all of the result set a small piece at a time, searching for the first or next viewable entry.
      Parameters:
      fetchLimit - the maximum number of sequential rows this iterator will request from Solr if, within those rows, no viewable results are found.
